{{Infobox person | name = Stephen Rannazzisi | image = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1977|7|4}} | birth_place = [[Smithtown, New York]], U.S. | occupation = Actor, stand-up comedian | alma_mater = [[State University of New York Oneonta]] | years_active = 2001–present | spouse =<!-- {{marriage|Tracy Rannazzisi|2006}}--> | children =<!-- 3--> | website = }} '''Stephen Rannazzisi''' (born July 4, 1977)<ref name=tvg>{{cite web| title=Stephen Rannazzisi| url=http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/stephen-rannazzisi/bio/271444/| publisher= [[TV Guide|TVGuide.com]] | accessdate=September 16, 2015}}</ref><ref>https://www.instagram.com/p/BWNhuXMj8bS/?taken-by=katieaselton&hl=en</ref> is an American actor, and stand-up comedian. He acted in the [[FXX (TV channel)|FXX]] comedy series ''[[The League]]'' as [[Fantasy football (American)|fantasy football]] league player Kevin MacArthur.
==Personal life== Rannazzisi, born in [[Smithtown, New York|Smithtown]], [[New York (state)|New York]] on July 4, 1977, briefly attended the Catholic [[St. Anthony's High School (New York)|St. Anthony's High School]] in [[South Huntington, New York]] on [[Long Island]], leaving after a year in what he called a mutual decision. He went on to graduate from [[Smithtown, New York#Smithtown High School|Smithtown High School]]<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.danspapers.com/2014/06/steve-rannazzisi-performs-at-bay-street-theater-monday/| title=Steve Rannazzisi Performs at Bay Street Theater Monday| date= June 27, 2014 |first=Brendan J. |last=O'Reilly | work = [[Dan's Papers]] | location =[[Southampton, New York]]|accessdate= September 16, 2015|archivedate= September 16, 2015| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150916191212/http://www.danspapers.com/2014/06/steve-rannazzisi-performs-at-bay-street-theater-monday/ |deadurl=no}}</ref> in 1996.<ref>{{cite web | url =http://smithtownhighschool.org/alumni/4428377/stephen-rannazzisi.html | title=Stephen Rannazzisi: Smithtown High Class of 1996 | publisher= Smithtown High School | accessdate= September 16, 2011}}</ref> Rannazzisi graduated from [[State University of New York at Oneonta]], where he majored in communications.<ref name=nyt>{{cite news| url =https://www.nytimes.com/2015/09/17/arts/television/steve-rannazzisi-comedian-who-told-of-9-11-escape-admits-he-lied.html |title=Steve Rannazzisi, Comedian Who Told of 9/11 Escape, Admits He Lied| first= Serge F. | last =Kovaleski| date= September 16, 2015| accessdate= September 16, 2015|work =[[The New York Times]]}}</ref> He is of Italian and Irish descent.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Donnelly|first1=Shawn|title=Steve Rannazzisi Talks World Cup, Italian Hair|url=http://www.mademan.com/steve-rannazzisi-talks-world-cup-italian-hair/|accessdate=28 May 2016}}</ref>
===9/11 Controversy=== For 14 years, Rannazzisi said he worked in the South Tower of the [[World Trade Center (1973–2001)|World Trade Center]] at [[Merrill Lynch]], on the 54th floor during the [[September 11 attacks]], and described his experience escaping death.<ref>{{cite podcast| url = http://www.wtfpod.com/podcast/episodes/episode_31_steve_rannazzisi_listener_email| title=WTF with Marc Maron: Episode 31 – Steve Rannazzisi / Listener Email| date=December 17, 2009| accessdate= September 16, 2015| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110521074332/http://www.wtfpod.com/podcast/episodes/episode_31_steve_rannazzisi_listener_email | archivedate= May 21, 2011|deadurl=no}} {{subscription}}</ref> <!---His future wife Tracy worked on the 24th floor, but was in mid-commute at the time of the attacks.--> He said the events inspired him to move to [[Los Angeles]] and pursue stand-up comedy. In September 2015, after being contacted by a reporter from ''[[The New York Times]]'' for an article debunking his claim,<ref name=nyt /> Rannazzisi admitted his story was a lie.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://twitter.com/SteveRannazzisi/status/644146873469546496| title=Center towers on 9/11....| publisher=Steve Rannazzisi verified [[Twitter]] account| date=September 16, 2015| accessdate=September 16, 2015| archivedate=September 16, 2015| archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6bapUYV3V?url=https://twitter.com/SteveRannazzisi| deadurl=no| df=}}</ref><ref>Rannazzisi, Twitter, [https://twitter.com/SteveRannazzisi/status/644147004856074240 "I don’t know why I said this."]</ref><ref>Rannazzisi, Twitter, [https://twitter.com/SteveRannazzisi/status/644147153565151232 "silence, I could somehow erase...."]</ref><ref>Rannazzisi, Twitter, [https://twitter.com/SteveRannazzisi/status/644147402652282882 "it is to the victims of 9/11...."]</ref> Rannazzisi was never employed by Merrill Lynch, which did not have offices in the World Trade Center then, and did not attend the [[State University of New York at Purchase]], as he additionally had claimed.<ref name=nyt />
